annotation.TEXT: I have to be even more accurate, but I'm doing alright so far.
Alright, I'll take it solo from here!
Nuts! Of course, the real trick is getting this to work! I can keep trying though.
Hmm... Better make sure I got all the koopas.
BGM: Sonic the Hedgehog 2 - Hill Top Zone
Now, I can't carry an item while in balloon form, so that's out of the question. I guess I'll need to fly.
Whoa! Unnecessarily risky toss there! But I got lucky!
What the...? Usually when I eat a shell that still has a koopa, the koopa is gone when I spit the shell out, but this time the koopa was still there!

Now, when shooting out of a cannon, you'll drop what you're holding, but it doesn't immediately vanish. So, just hold left (and the run and jump buttons if you want) and you can go back and pick it up again!
Now, I didn't go for the flower earlier, because I usually ended up accidentally frying my shell prematurely!
Alright, now that I have a cape, I'm going to backtrack for a flower, which I'll want for later.
Baby Yoshi (and Red Yoshi too, for that matter) would be useless for this challenge anyway!
Another miss! This is tricky!
The fuzzies complicate things just a little bit.
Whoa! That was weird! Did the invisible Yoshi just run off? Let's ditch the other one and find out!
Nice!
Jackpot! It's been a while since I got 50 without tool-assistance!
Getting all five parakoopas here is quite simple actually!
Almost!
Gotta be careful here. It's really easy to lose the shell if you're reckless!
Hmm... How am I going to get that guy? Looks really tricky!
Well, let's first clear out the rest of the enemies first, then I'll come back here.
Yes! Got it! Now the rest is quite simple!
Gotcha!
It's easy enough to make him respawn so I can get another shot at him, though.
Hi, Yoshi!
Side areas are only required if it is possible to keep the shell through the area.
Well, that was an odd way to kick the shell. I've sure been encountering a lot of oddities in this challenge!
Alright, I'm done here. I'll just roast the shell now and then be on my way.
SMW challenge from cheez8Productions: Enter one level in each of five different worlds. In each level, take a shell and use it to kill all other enemies, then turn the shell into a coin at the end.
Alright, time for some glitchy goodness!
This may seem easy, but it's actually very tricky. There are so many ways to screw up! So, I'm using savestates between levels.
Now maybe I could pull off that stunt again here, but I don't want to press my luck and risk landing on a whammy this time!
Alright, let's switch back to the cape and take off!
Well, I'm done with this level. Let's get out of here!
Awesome!
The last five over the pit seem tricky, but aren't actually that hard. Just don't try to hit them all in one go.
Whew! That was close!
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Underground
For this next part, I'm going to have a little fun! This is tricky, but I'm pretty good at it!
Hi, Yoshi! Bye, Yoshi!
But now that I have a cape, I can just keep the flower in reserve until needed.
BGM: Fire Emblem - Together We Ride
And that's the last foe, so I'll just fry this shell and finish the level!
Now, seriously, who would even bother with this particular side area unless they're on a challenge? There's nothing here but a bunch of pipes and two parakoopas.
One time I even lost the shell simply because the paragoomba changed direction on me suddenly! I'm ready for it this time, though!
Much better!
BGM: Sonic the Hedgehog - Green Hill Zone
Nuts. I missed that parachute goomba, and I have to hit him, because that one's not from a generator.
So... I take it that invisible Yoshis don't like it when I pick up a shell? How odd.
Bye, Yoshi!
And I know that there's only seven parakoopas there, so there's no need to double-check.
Wow! I just got incredibly lucky there! I missed the midair catch, but the shell landed nicely on the block AND took out the fuzzy!
Barf!
Sweet!
Well, that didn't go well. Let's just make it respawn and try again!
29!? What is this crap!? Well, whatever. This challenge is now complete!
And it's not even a shortcut either! You return to the main area about half a screen from where you entered this area. I wonder if Nintendo meant to put coins in here or something, but forgot...
Now, in this level, I have to aim accurately multiple times! And yes, I've had to retry this level several times before I got it right!
Honestly, I don't know why I had Yoshi wait way over there, when I could've easily just flown over here! I'd better hurry back before Yoshi swallows my shell!
I guess you can tag along for a little while.
Now this side area is not as pointless since it has a Yoshi Coin in it. Also, it's a fun place for koopa stomping (but I'm not here for that)!
And that was the last foe, so I'll just turn the shell into a coin with a fireball, then finish the level!
Yet another oddity: That spiny turned around because it bumped into the shell, but the shell was still moving, so how come the spiny didn't get whacked?
Getting to the keyhole ledge isn't too hard if you know how.
Hi, Yoshi!
This part's tricky. Several times I lost the shell in some way here (usually by crashing it into a goomba).
Hi, Yoshi!
Now, just like with the parachute goomba generator in the last level, I only have to kill one of the parachute Bob-ombs here.
Wow, what a crappy take off! Let's try that again, shall we?
Hi, Yoshi!
Miss! But at least I didn't lose the shell.
But, how am I going to hit that koopa with the shell without losing the shell? Well, there is a way, but it's very tricky!
You know what? I'm sorry Yoshi, but I'm going to have to leave you behind. It's a lot easier to do this without you.
Yeah, I got 'em all.
If I do enter a side area, I don't have to bother rekilling enemies in the main area that I've already killed once before.
Gotta aim carefully here.
Hmm... I wonder if I can get 50 twice in a row...
Yoshi, stay here for a moment, and don't swallow my shell!
Let's see if I can nail all seven parakoopas in one shot!
When it comes to enemy generators (like the parachute goomba generator here), killing just one of them is good enough.
BGM: Ninja Gaiden NES - Ryu's Determination
BGM: Air Man Ga Taosenai
Now, I don't see any way off of this ledge, but who said I had to use the normal exit?
